1 toxin, destructive substance, or destructive device in, upon, near, or on
2 board any rail infrastructure;
3 (d) Detaches, initiates an emergency brake application of, or
4 otherwise interferes with the movement of, any train, locomotive, freight
5 or passenger car, or any other on-track vehicle or equipment;
6 (e) Assaults or injures any rail passenger, railroad employee, or
7 police officer of a railroad or any person on or within any railroad
8 property;
9 (f) Makes a terroristic threat or knowingly conveys false
10 information or reports regarding an attempt or alleged attempt to commit
11 any of the acts described in this subsection; or
12 (g) Attempts, threatens, or conspires with others to commit any of
13 the acts described in this subsection.
14 (3) A violation of this section is a Class IIIA felony.
15 Sec. 3. Original section 28-101, Revised Statutes Cumulative
16 Supplement, 2024, is repealed.
